1 Section 1000.23. A. The Oklahoma Uniform Building Code
2 Commission shall have the power and the duty to review and adopt all
3 building codes and standards for residential and commercial
4 construction to be used by all entities within this state. Codes
5 and standards adopted by the Commission shall be the minimum
6 standards for residential and commercial construction in this state.
7 B. All public projects shall abide by such minimum standards
8 and requirements; provided, nothing in the Oklahoma Uniform Building
9 Code Commission Act shall prevent or take away from state agencies
10 the authority to enact and enforce requirements containing higher
11 standards and requirements than such minimum standards and
12 requirements.
13 C. Municipalities and other political subdivisions shall abide
14 by such minimum standards and requirements; provided, nothing in the
15 Oklahoma Uniform Building Code Commission Act shall prevent or take
16 away from such municipalities and other political subdivisions the
17 authority to enact and enforce requirements containing higher
18 standards and requirements than such minimum standards and
19 requirements.
20 D. The Oklahoma Uniform Building Code Commission shall have the
21 power and duty to establish a continuing education and training and
